What Color?
Privacy Policy
Introduction
Welcome to What Color? ("we", "our", "us"). We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring that your personal information is handled in a safe and responsible manner. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our app and services.
Information We Collect
Anonymous Usage
You can use our app completely anonymously without logging in. In this mode, we do not collect any personal information from you.
Logged-In Usage
If you choose to log in, we use Auth0 to authenticate your identity. The information we collect during the login process includes:
Email address
Nickname
Data Collected Automatically
When you use our app, whether logged in or anonymously, we may collect certain information automatically, including:
IP address
Device type
Operating system
App usage data
We use the following external services to collect and analyze this data:
Google Analytics
: For tracking and analyzing app usage.
Mixpanel
: For tracking user interactions and app performance.
Sentry
: For error tracking and improving app functionality.
How We Use Your Information
Anonymous Users
If you use the app anonymously, we only collect non-personal usage data to improve the app's performance and user experience.
Logged-In Users
If you log in, we use your information to:
Authenticate your identity via Auth0.
Provide personalized features and services.
Improve our app and services based on user interactions and feedback.
Denial of Tracking
You have the option to deny tracking for analytics when you log in. If you choose to deny tracking, we will not collect or use your data for analytics purposes.
Sharing Your Information
We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your personal information to outside parties except as described below:
Auth0
: For authentication services.
Google Analytics
: For usage tracking and analytics.
Mixpanel
: For user interaction tracking and performance analysis.
Sentry
: For error tracking and app functionality improvements.
These third-party services have their own privacy policies, which you can review on their respective websites.
Data Security
We implement a variety of security measures to maintain the safety of your personal information. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
Your Rights
You have the right to:
Access the personal data we hold about you.
Request the correction of incorrect or incomplete data.
Request the deletion of your personal data.
Object to the processing of your personal data.
Withdraw consent at any time if we are processing your data based on consent.
To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at
support@whatcolor.dev
.
Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.
Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
Email:
support@whatcolor.dev